Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Olivia speaking. Who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 2: Adrian Villarreal.

Speaker 1: Hi, Adrian. How are you?

Speaker 2: Okay, and you?

Speaker 1: Good. I'm good. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, I need to cancel my subscription for a while.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah, I can help you with that. What is your date of birth, Adrian?

Speaker 2: 2-26-1973.

Speaker 1: Great, and you're located at 709 West 209th Street in Torrance, California?

Speaker 2: Precisely, yes.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so you always have the option if you don't want to continue to receive those regular monthly refills to place your prescription on hold for up to 6 months at a time just because 6 months is when the prescription would expire if we didn't refill it.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And then if you did want to order before then, you could. You just have to give us a call to place the order yourself at any point that you would be ready before July 23rd.

Speaker 2: Oh, I didn't know I had that option.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah.

Speaker 2: Because I went online and I didn't see that option on there when I was on there and right now I'm on my phone so I can't go on there. But yeah, I went online and I didn't see that option but I might have missed it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so yeah, I placed your prescription on hold until the last week of July so if you need anything before then or whenever you are ready to order again, just give us a call to place the order before then.

Speaker 2: Okay, cool, perfect. So I won't be charged until I call back, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah, the prescription is on hold until then, yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, perfect. That's all I want to do. So I'll give you another call before then but I cannot be charged until I call you back.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no monthly charges, correct.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect. Okay, great. Well, thank you, Adrian.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much for your help. I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, have a great day.

Speaker 2: Same to you. Thank you. Bye-bye.
